{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect enum assignment in UL TDA info mapping type\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_ul_tda_info` function in nr_mac_common.c was directly assigning uint8_t values from PUSCH time domain allocation tables to the mapping_type enum field. This could cause data corruption when the uint8_t values don't exactly match the enum constants.\n\nThe fix converts the table values to proper enum values using explicit conditional checks.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Added proper enum conversion in get_ul_tda_info function\n- Lines 544 and 549 now use (table_value == 0) ? typeA : typeB pattern instead of direct assignment\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain RNTI configurations where the TDA tables are used instead of RRC configured lists, the mapping_type field could end up with invalid values. This might manifest as:\n- Incorrect PUSCH mapping type interpretation\n- Potential scheduling conflicts\n- Unexpected behavior in UL transmission timing\n\nThe issue is more likely to occur in FR2 configurations or when using specific PRACH configurations that trigger the default table path.\n"
}